# ESP32-S3 iPod Haptic Feedback - KiCad Schematic Template

## This is a template/reference for creating the actual KiCad schematic
## Copy this content as a starting point for your KiCad project

# Component List and Connections

## ESP32-S3 Module (U1)
# ESP32-S3-WROOM-1 or ESP32-S3-DevKitC-1
# Power: 3.3V
# Programming: USB-C connector

## Power Management (U2)
# AMS1117-3.3 Voltage Regulator
# Input: 5V from USB-C
# Output: 3.3V for system

## Display Interface (J1)
# 9-pin header for ILI9341 display
# SPI connection to ESP32-S3

## Haptic Driver (U3)
# DRV2605L Haptic Motor Driver
# I2C connection to ESP32-S3
# LRA output connector

## Button Interface (SW1-SW4)
# 4x Tactile push buttons
# Pull-up resistors to 3.3V

## Connectors
# J1: Display connector (9-pin)
# J2: USB-C programming/power
# J3: LRA connector (2-pin)
# J4: Battery connector (optional, 2-pin JST)

# Net Connections

## Power Nets
# +5V: USB input, regulator input
# +3V3: System power rail
# GND: Ground reference

## ESP32-S3 Connections
# GPIO8  -> TFT_RST
# GPIO9  -> TFT_DC
# GPIO10 -> TFT_CS
# GPIO11 -> SPI_MOSI
# GPIO12 -> SPI_CLK
# GPIO13 -> SPI_MISO
# GPIO14 -> BTN_MENU
# GPIO15 -> BTN_PLAY
# GPIO16 -> BTN_PREV
# GPIO17 -> BTN_NEXT
# GPIO21 -> I2C_SDA
# GPIO22 -> I2C_SCL

## Display Connections (J1)
# Pin 1: GND
# Pin 2: +3V3 (VCC)
# Pin 3: +3V3 (LED)
# Pin 4: TFT_RST
# Pin 5: TFT_DC
# Pin 6: TFT_CS
# Pin 7: SPI_MOSI
# Pin 8: SPI_CLK
# Pin 9: SPI_MISO

## DRV2605L Connections (U3)
# VIN -> +3V3
# GND -> GND
# SDA -> I2C_SDA
# SCL -> I2C_SCL
# OUT+ -> LRA_P
# OUT- -> LRA_N

## Button Connections
# SW1 (Menu): GPIO14 -> Button -> GND, Pull-up to +3V3
# SW2 (Play): GPIO15 -> Button -> GND, Pull-up to +3V3
# SW3 (Prev): GPIO16 -> Button -> GND, Pull-up to +3V3
# SW4 (Next): GPIO17 -> Button -> GND, Pull-up to +3V3

# Component Values

## Resistors (0805 package)
# R1-R4: 10kΩ (Button pull-ups)
# R5-R6: 4.7kΩ (I2C pull-ups)
# R7: 330Ω (Power LED current limiting)
# R8: 330Ω (Status LED current limiting)

## Capacitors
# C1: 220μF electrolytic (Regulator input)
# C2: 100μF electrolytic (Regulator output)
# C3-C6: 100nF ceramic 0805 (Decoupling)
# C7-C8: 10μF tantalum 1206 (Power rail filtering)

## LEDs (0805 package)
# LED1: Green (Power indicator)
# LED2: Blue (Status indicator)

## Connectors
# J1: 2.54mm pitch header 1x9 (Display)
# J2: USB-C connector (Power/Programming)
# J3: JST PH 2-pin (LRA connection)
# J4: JST PH 2-pin (Battery, optional)

# PCB Layout Notes

## Layer Stack (2-layer)
# Top: Components, signals, power traces
# Bottom: Ground plane, return paths

## Trace Widths
# Power (3.3V, 5V): 0.5mm (20mil)
# Signals: 0.2mm (8mil)
# Ground: Plane + fills

## Component Placement
# ESP32-S3: Center of board
# DRV2605L: Near ESP32-S3
# Buttons: Corners for case mounting
# Connectors: Board edges
# Decoupling caps: Near IC power pins

## Design Rules
# Minimum trace: 0.15mm (6mil)
# Minimum via: 0.2mm (8mil)
# Minimum clearance: 0.15mm (6mil)

# Manufacturing Specifications
# Board size: 100mm x 60mm
# Thickness: 1.6mm
# Copper: 1oz (35μm)
# Solder mask: Green
# Silkscreen: White
# Surface finish: HASL or ENIG

# Assembly Notes
# SMD components on top side
# Through-hole components (buttons, connectors)
# Hand assembly or SMT service
# Reflow profile for lead-free solder

# Testing Points
# TP1: +3V3 rail
# TP2: +5V rail  
# TP3: GND
# TP4: I2C_SDA
# TP5: I2C_SCL
# TP6: SPI_CLK
# TP7: TFT_CS

# This template provides the foundation for creating the actual KiCad schematic
# Import this structure into KiCad and add proper symbols and footprints